eply. And just in-case you aren’t available right away, you can set up an auto-reply so your customers get an immediate response.\n\n![SendBoard overview - collaborate](https://app.sendboard.com/images/sendboard-how-2.png)\n\n**Reply**\n\nWhen you are ready to reply, you can put together a rich-text email with attachments. You can also set up an email signature to be magically added to all of your future replies.\n\n![SendBoard overview - reply](https://app.sendboard.com/images/sendboard-how-3.png)\n\nSo that’s a brief summary of how the Power-Up works: Receive emails, collaborate, and then reply - all from within Trello.\n\n------------\n\n\n## Getting Started\n\n-  **Activate the Power-Up**- Firstly, add the SendBoard Power-Up to a Trello board.\n- **Forward your emails** - Configure your email to forward to your SendBoard account.\n- **Customise SendBoard** - Set up auto-replies, email forwarding rules and more.\n\n----------\n\n## Public Beta\n\nSendBoard will be in Public Beta until January 2020. Until then, the product will be free for unlimited boards and users. In January, we will be introducing our paid plans. For customers that sign up before then, the monthly charge will be $19 per board for unlimited users.\n\nWe have an exciting roadmap of features we are working through. And we'd love to hear your feedback as you start using the product. If you have any suggestions or run into any issues, please get in touch with us by contacting hello@sendboard.com.\n\n----------\n\n## Legal\n\nBy activating this Power-Up, you agree to the [Terms of Service](https://www.sendboard.com/terms) and [Privacy Policy](https://www.sendboard.com/privacy).\n\n----------\n\n![SendBoard](https://www.google-analytics.com/collect?v=1&tid=UA-134696442-1&cid=555&aip=1&t=event&ec=Trello%20Directory&ea=View%20Power-Up%20Listing&dp=%2Ftrello%2Fpower-up-listing&dt=SendBoard)\n\n","overview":"An email helpdesk in Trello. Teams can receive emails, collaborate and reply — right from within 